  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b8e\u0bb5\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc7 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b90.\u0ba8\u0bbe.",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Countries should decide how to deal with crises - UN",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "We are witnessing the worst happenings in Sri Lanka right now. This is a warning signal to other countries.",
        "Achim Schreiner, director of the United Nations Development Programme, pointed out that it is up to the respective countries to find out how to deal with this crisis appropriately.",
        "Apart from that, he pointed out that all countries globally are facing the pressure of the economic crisis caused by the spread of the corona virus, and the threat caused by this is similar to the economic and human rights situation in Sri Lanka.",
        "He said the above while participating in a discussion organized by the United Nations in Geneva to present recommendations regarding the actions to be taken and the policies to be formulated by the international countries to properly deal with the global food, fuel and financial crises.",
        "He mentioned the above about Sri Lanka while quoting about the country in South Asia that was forced to pay back its debts.",
        "He also pointed out that 'indebtedness is not only the inability of a country to repay its debts, but also the inability to import essential commodities, be it petrol, diesel or medicine, which are essential to keep the country's economy alive and functioning'.",
        "At the same time, Jorge Gray Molina, Senior Economist of the United Nations Development Program, who expressed his opinion in this current discussion, said, 'After the spread of the Corona virus, although the effects of the impact on the workforce and income, complete paralysis can be observed, they have had a massive impact on a long-term basis.",
        "In the last 18 months, around 125 million people have been affected by poverty globally, and now we can observe that the inflation of about 3 months has pushed 71 million people into poverty."
      ],
